Most world series are very evenly divided and won by a single game. I dont know anything about baseball but I would expect to have a 3-4 or 4-3 outcome.
I'm getting in late, but the Astros have won one game already. No major injuries. Their confidence is high and solid. and it's baseball, so a lot of things can happen in the next five games.

Updating post-Game 2. The two teams seem to be fairly evenly matched, and the Astros might have a slight edge (they had more hits than Philadelphia in both games so far). A shut-out of the Astros going forward seems VERY unlikely and 3 or 4 wins seem to be the overwhelmingly likely outcomes at this point.

On one hand 538 gives a 68% chance to Astros. Astros won 4 of the last 6 World Series, am I right? That's 63% chance for Astros according to Laplace's rule of succession. On the other hand, the betting world has ~70% of its bets on the Phillies (which makes sense because many people bet on the underdog to make a huge profit) and only 55% of all the money is on the Astros. Further, the last 10 games' points per game metric is higher for the Phillies than for the Astros. So in a nutshell, Astros are the favorite in terms of betting and data, but not as strongly as their past history, latest history, and what this current GJO crowd consensus is saying.
Ok, I’ll take a swing at it…
